# 6. まるで、SHINOBI

Commentator: <Alright, the baton's been passed to our ninth group's second competitor!>
Akito: (I have to finish in under forty seconds if we still want to keep our hopes of winning alive.)
Akito: (The water spider is going to eat up a lot of my time, so I have to save as much as I can during the high vault...)
Akito: (So...)
Commentator: <Okay, there's the high vault! Our competitor will need to launch himself over eight layers to succeed.>
Akito: (I have to get it right the first time if I'm going to post the fastest time possible.)
Akito: (Build up a lot of momentum and... Three, two, one...)
Akito: (Now!)
Akito: Hup!
Commentator: <A beautiful jump! He cleared it on his first try!>
Haruka: (Yes...! Those jumping squats really paid off!)
Tsukasa: Nice one, Akito!
An: Keep it up!
Commentator: <Next, we have the water spider! In front of our competitor is a pool that's eight meters wide and fifteen meters long!>
Commentator: <He'll need to stand on a pair of special inner tubes in order to cross, with only a pole to help support him. But he's done well so far! How quickly can he finish?!>
Akito: (The straps on these inner tubes are a bit loose. I'll need to keep that in mind...)
Akito: (I want to finish fast, but is it worth taking a big risk? No, don't rush. Slow and steady wins the race!)
Haruka: (The waiting area's right next to the water spider stage. I can see clearly see what's happening.)
Haruka: (Shinonome's doing... Good, he's moving at a decent speed... He's also conserving energy by staying calm.)
Akito: (Two meters to go. I just gotta keep this up and...)
Akito: ...?!
Commentator: <Wait, he's stopped all of a sudden! Is something wrong?>
Haruka: (What's going on? He's looking down at his left foot. It's still above the water...)
Haruka: ...! What if...?!
Haruka: (I knew it! The strap broke...!)
Haruka: (This is bad. He'll have trouble just staying standing, let alone moving forward.)
Haruka: (All he has at this point are his right foot and the pole. How is he supposed to get to the finish line now...?)
Haruka: (I know!)
Haruka: Shinonome!
Akito: Kiritani?
Haruka: Use the other inner tube as an oar! Propel yourself forward by pushing against it!
Haruka: (He only has one foot and that pole now, so it won't be easy for him to maintain his balance... But I'm sure he can do this!)
Akito: She's joking, right?
Akito: But I don't have much of a choice at this point...
Tsukasa: Oh! He's back to moving!
Audience: Whoa! He's using only one foot!
Audience: But he's staying afloat... He's using that pole to keep his balance, while using the other inner tube as an oar!
Audience: He's like a real ninja!
An: Way to go, Akito!
Akito: (My foot's going to sink if I lose focus for even a second... I have to carefully shift my weight, while maintaining this posture!)
Akito: (The other side's right there...! I just gotta keep this up...!)
Commentator: <He finished! Despite what happened, he was able to cross to the other side!>
Commentator: <He's taken the inner tubes off, and is now running towards his teammate!>
Akito: Kiritani! We're counting on you!
Akito: Go! Fly!
Commentator: <Our ninth group's hopes now rest with their final competitor! She's using the momentum her teammate created in order to absolutely fly!>
Haruka: (Despite Tenma and Shinonome running into some trouble, we're still in contention. If I do well here, we might just win... No, not might.)
Haruka: (We will win. I can't let their efforts go to waste!)
Commentator: <Alright, she's reached the wall she'll be climbing!>
Haruka: (Five meters... This is very similar to bouldering. I need to choose where to place my hands and feet carefully.)
Haruka: (The quickest route to the top is...)
Haruka: (There!)
Audience: Sh-She's so fast...!
Audience: Yeah, and she's got her route all figured out! She's basically going straight up it!
Audience: Wait a second... Isn't that Haruka Kiritani?! What's she doing here?!
An: Haha... Looks like your cover's blown, Haruka...
Akito's Voice: To be fair, we are talking about a former top-flight idol going rock climbing.
An: Huh...?
An: Hey! You guys did awesome! And Haruka looks like she's on a roll!
Akito: Yeah. She's probably on track to be fastest among all the teams right now.
Tsukasa: Probably. We might actually be able to win this.
Haruka: Huff... Huff...
Haruka: (I didn't have any issues climbing that wall, so my current time should be pretty good.)
Haruka: (Which just leaves...)
Commentator: <She's reached the final obstacle! How much time will she need to clear it?! Let's hope that she doesn't disqualify herself by falling in!>
Commentator: <Her final test! The hanging poles!>
